# Core Execution Logic

## Step 1: Dimension-Based Compliance Check

Validate code/config against 10 performance dimensions and mark compliance status with evidence:

| Dimension | Validation Criteria |
| --- | --- |
| 1. Performance Metric Monitoring | - Integrated FP/FCP/LCP monitoring via Paint Timing API<br>- Used Lighthouse/Chrome DevTools for baseline testing<br>- Configured Network "Disable Cache" + Coverage analysis |
| 2. Network Layer Optimization | - Enabled HTTP2/HTTP3 (vs HTTP1.1 head-of-line blocking)<br>- Configured CDN for static assets + DNS Prefetch/Preconnect<br>- Added Preload/modulepreload for critical resources<br>- Enabled gzip/brotli compression (server + build)<br>- Cached CORS preflight with `Access-Control-Max-Age` |
| 3. Resource Loading Optimization | - Implemented Code Splitting (route lazy loading)<br>- Enabled Tree Shaking<br>- Configured `Cache-Control: max-age=31536000`<br>- Build artifacts with hash filenames (e.g., app.89fd213.js)<br>- Image optimization (WebP, lazy loading, compression)<br>- On-demand 3rd-party imports (e.g., lodash single methods) |
| 4. Build Phase Optimization | - Enabled JS/CSS/HTML minification (Terser/Cssnano)<br>- Split Chunks (vendor/business/runtime)<br>- No devDependencies in production dependencies<br>- Used bundle analyzers (rollup-plugin-visualizer) |
| 5. CSS Loading Optimization | - Critical CSS inlined in `<style>`<br>- Non-critical CSS loaded async via `media="print"`<br>- Removed unused CSS (Coverage analysis)<br>- All CSS bundled in `<head>` |
| 6. JS Execution Optimization | - `<script>` with `async/defer` (no HTML parse blocking)<br>- Non-critical JS at body end<br>- Split long tasks (>10ms) + `requestIdleCallback`<br>- Web Worker for heavy computation<br>- Event delegation for fewer listeners |
| 7. Browser Rendering Optimization | - Batch DOM ops with DocumentFragment<br>- Animations use `transform/opacity` (composite layer only)<br>- Avoid frequent style changes (use class instead)<br>- `requestAnimationFrame` for smooth animations |
| 8. FPS Optimization | - JS execution < 10ms per frame (60FPS target)<br>- Removed long tasks causing jank<br>- Monitored/reduced layout/paint frequency |
| 9. User Experience Optimization | - Implemented skeleton screens<br>- Enabled lazy loading (images/components)<br>- Configured SSR/streaming rendering (if applicable) |
| 10. Cache Strategy | - HTTP cache + build hash double-layer strategy<br>- Valid cache invalidation (hash changes on content update) |

## Step 2: Extract Issue List

List non-compliant items with:

- Exact location (file/line: e.g., `index.html:5 <script> missing defer`)
- Impact dimension (e.g., "JS Execution Optimization")
- Impact level (Core/Secondary/Experience)

## Step 3: Actionable Optimization Suggestions

For each issue, provide:

- Step-by-step implementation
- Full code/config examples
- Expected performance gain (e.g., "LCP reduced by 30%")

## Step 4: Priority Ranking

Sort issues by impact:

1. **Core (Must Fix)**: Block first paint/LCP, cause jank (FPS drop)
2. **Secondary (Recommended Fix)**: Increase bundle size, inefficient caching
3. **Experience (Optional)**: Skeleton screens, minor UX tweaks

